===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|dyew}}
From {{m|en|hodiern|t=of this day, present-day}} + [[w:English language|English]] {{m|en|-al|pos=suffix forming {{glossary|adjective}}s}}.<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=adj|id=87548|date=1899|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=adj}}</ref> ''Hodiern'' is derived from {{der|en|la|hodiernus|t=of today, today’s; present, present-day; actual}}, from {{m|la|hodiē|t=today}} (from {{m|la|hōc|t=this (thing)}} + {{m|la|diēs|diē|day}} (ultimately {{der|en|ine-pro|*dyew-|t=to be bright; heaven, sky}})) + {{m|la|-rnus|pos=suffix forming adjectives}}.

